Interface DataControllerAsio.Listener

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    DataController.Listener
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConnectionStatusReceiver
    Enclosing class:
    DataControllerAsio

    public static interface DataControllerAsio.Listener
    Provides information on the status of live and stored data.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void liveDataConnected()
      Indicates that a connection has been established all the way to a live data source (possibly through multiple data servers).
      void liveDataConnectError(java.lang.String msg)
      When live data is disconnected, the underlying live data provider will attempt to reconnect.
      void liveDataDisconnected()
      Indicates that a the connection to a live data source has been lost (temporarily).
      void stopped()
      Notifies that all live and stored data have stopped.
      void storedDataBegin()
      Stored data have begun to be fetched from one or more type controllers.
      void storedDataEnd()
      The fetching of stored data has completed.
      void storedDataError(java.lang.String msg)
      Called when some stored data fetching failed, typically due to a connection error.
      void storedDataProgress(float progress)
      An estimation of the fraction (from 0 to 1) of stored data that have completed.

    • Method Detail

      • liveDataConnected

        void liveDataConnected()
        Indicates that a connection has been established all the way to a live data source (possibly through multiple data servers).

      • liveDataDisconnected

        void liveDataDisconnected()
        Indicates that a the connection to a live data source has been lost (temporarily).

      • liveDataConnectError

        void liveDataConnectError(java.lang.String msg)
        When live data is disconnected, the underlying live data provider will attempt to reconnect. Every time a connection attempt tails, this method will be called.
        Parameters:
        msg - a short description of the error

      • storedDataBegin

        void storedDataBegin()
        Stored data have begun to be fetched from one or more type controllers.

      • storedDataEnd

        void storedDataEnd()
        The fetching of stored data has completed. If live data are enabled, more stored data may be fetched later.

      • storedDataProgress

        void storedDataProgress(float progress)
        An estimation of the fraction (from 0 to 1) of stored data that have completed.
        Parameters:
        progress - a completion measure between 0 and 1

      • storedDataError

        void storedDataError(java.lang.String msg)
        Called when some stored data fetching failed, typically due to a connection error.
        Parameters:
        msg - a short description of the error

      • stopped

        void stopped()
        Notifies that all live and stored data have stopped.
